import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='time')
    avg_duration = data['time'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_duration, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Duration: {avg_duration:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average flight duration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
